This file documents the revision history for Perl distribution
`Games-DateTime`.


VERSION HISTORY
===============

0.00 : Released on 2009-12-XX (JST)
-----------------------------------

Initial release.
(not for CPAN)

### Features

#### `Games::DateTime`

-   Implemented `Games::DateTime`,
    which treats date and time on calendars of any games
    as an object oriented interfaces.

#### Implementations and aliases

-   Implemented `Games::DateTime::Implementation::EQ1` and
    `Games::DateTime::Alias::EQ1`,
    which treat the calendar on Norrath: the world of EverQuest.

-   Implemented `Games::DateTime::Implementation::EQ2` and
    `Games::DateTime::Alias::EQ2`,
    which treat the calendar on Norrath: the world of EverQuest II.

-   Implemented `Games::DateTime::Implementation::FF11` and
    `Games::DateTime::Alias::FF11`,
    which treat the calendar called Crystal Era (C.E.)
    on Vana'diel: the world of Final Fantasy XI.

-   Implemented `Games::DateTime::Implementation::FF14` and
    `Games::DateTime::Alias::FF14`,
    which are a place holder.

-   Implemented `Games::DateTime::Implementation::WoW` and
    `Games::DateTime::Alias::WoW`,
    which are a place holder.

### Tests

-   Prepared tests for `Games::DateTime`.

### Documents

-   Prepared minimal documents.


META INFORMATION
================

Version notation
----------------

    V.vvrr_dd : Released on YYYY-MM-DD (Time Zone)

### V  : Major version number

-   Added ambitious features
-   Changed in APIs
    (older API will be keeped to compatibility for a some period)
-   ...

### vv : Minor version number (in major version)

-   Added several features
-   Improved any features
-   Fixed bugs
-   ...

### rr : Revision number (in minor version, on demand)

You would not need to update the distribution.

-   Improved tests
-   Updated documents
-   ...

### dd : Developer release number (in revision number, on demand)

This is unstable version.
Unless you are a developer, You will not be recommended to upgrade
the distribution.

-   Added experimental features
-   Fixed bugs provisionally
-   ...


Document format
---------------

This `Changes` file was formatted in Markdown.

    % perl -MText::Markdown -MFile::Slurp \
      -e 'print (Text::Markdown->new->markdown(scalar read_file(q{Changes})));'
